# WHAT IT IS
#   `mnotify` is a **single-binary command-line Matrix client**
#   designed to make Matrix usable from shell pipelines:  send a
#   message into a Matrix room as part of a shell script's
#   completion notification, dump room messages as JSON for jq
#   post-processing, list joined rooms for filtering, redact a
#   specific event, react to emoji-verification challenges
#   non-interactively, or run a long-lived `mnotify sync` that
#   prints every received timeline event as JSON.
#
#   It maintains a persistent session in the standard XDG
#   directories (`$XDG_DATA_HOME/mnotify/...`), stores the access
#   token securely in the system keychain (via the `keyring`
#   crate), and supports the **full Matrix end-to-end encryption
#   stack** via `matrix-sdk-crypto` (Olm + Megolm + SAS / QR-code
#   verification + key-backup / cross-signing).  Sliding sync
#   (`experimental-sliding-sync` feature) is enabled by default
#   for lightweight syncing against Element X-compatible
#   homeservers.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/main.rs clap-derive
#                       `Cli` struct + `Command` enum;
#                       extracted via raw.githubusercontent.com
#                       fetch of src/main.rs)
#
#   mnotify [GLOBAL OPTIONS] <COMMAND>
#
#   Global options:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Print version
#     -v, --verbose                  Increase verbosity
#                                    (repeatable;  from
#                                    clap-verbosity-flag)
#     -q, --quiet                    Decrease verbosity
#                                    (repeatable)
#     -f, --full-state               Request the full state
#                                    during sync
#     -p, --presense <STATE>         Presence value while syncing
#                                    [default: online]
#                                    [values: online, offline,
#                                     unavailable]
#
#   Commands:
#     clean <USER_ID>                Delete session store and
#                                    secrets (dangerous!)
#                                    USER_ID: full Matrix
#                                    user-ID `@alice:example.org`
#     homeserver | hs                Get information about your
#                                    homeserver and login
#         -f, --force                Really print the token
#         -t, --token                Include the bearer token
#                                    in the JSON output
#     login <USER_ID>                Log in to a homeserver and
#                                    create a session store
#         -p, --password <PW>        Password  (prompted if not
#                                    provided)
#         -d, --device-name <NAME>   Device name  [default:
#                                    `mnotify`]
#     logout                         Log out and delete all state
#     messages -r <ROOM_ID>          Dump messages of a room
#         -l, --limit <N>            Number of events  [default:
#                                    10]
#     redact -r <ROOM_ID> -e <EVENT_ID>
#                                    Redact a specific event
#         --reason <STR>             Redaction reason
#     rooms [--room-id <ID>]         Query room information
#                                    (all joined rooms if no
#                                    --room-id)
#     send -r <ROOM_ID> [OPTIONS] [MESSAGE]
#                                    Send a message to a room
#         -m, --markdown             Enable markdown formatting
#         -n, --notice               Send as a notice message
#         -e, --emote                Send as an emote message
#                                    (conflicts with --notice)
#         -a, --attachment <PATH>    Send a file as attachment
#                                    (conflicts with MESSAGE)
#         --reply-to <EVENT_ID>      Reply to a specific
#                                    event_id  (conflicts with
#                                    --notice, --emote,
#                                    --attachment)
#         MESSAGE                    Text to send (read from
#                                    stdin if omitted)
#     sync                           Run a sync and print all
#                                    events
#         --room-id <ID>             Limit to one room
#         --receipt                  Mark all received messages
#                                    as read
#         --raw                      Print raw sync events as
#                                    they come
#     typing --room-id <ID>          Send typing notifications
#         --disable                  Disable typing instead of
#                                    enabling
#     verify                         React to emoji verification
#                                    requests
#     whoami                         Ask the homeserver who we
#                                    are
#
